  <title>Using an External DITA Open Toolkit in <ph keyref="product"/></title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>DITA<indexterm>Use external DITA-OT</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody>
    <context>
      <p id="p_vrn_dgk_54b"><ph keyref="product"/> comes bundled with a DITA Open Toolkit, located
        in the <filepath><term keyref="glossentry_dita_ot_dir"/></filepath> directory. If you want
        to use an external DITA-OT for all transformations and validations, you can <ph
          conkeyref="reusables-preferences-pages/open-the-preferences-page"/> and go to <xref
          href="preferences-dita.dita#preferences-dita">the <uicontrol>DITA</uicontrol> page</xref>,
        where you can specify the DITA-OT to be used.</p>
    </context>
